article.headline: Siena 64, N.J. Tech 40
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. (AP) -- Michael Haddix scored a game-high 13 points, leading three double-figure scorers, as Siena defeated New Jersey Institute of Technology 64-40 Monday night. David Ryan added 12 points and Edwin Ubiles scored 11 for the Saints (2-2). Clayton Barker and Marc Milbourne Swan led NJIT (2-3) with 10 points apiece as the Highlanders were held to a season-low scoring total. Siena used three-quarter court pressure and an aggressive matchup zone to stymie the NJIT offense. The Highlanders shot just 26 percent and committed 16 turnovers in the first half as Siena surged to a 30-15 halftime lead. NJIT closed the gap to 33-24 on Milbourne Swan's layup with 16:04 left, but Siena responded with eight unanswered points -- four by Ubiles -- over the next 3:13 and was never seriously threatened again.
